The old saying to handle yourself is strong, as is the feeling of being perceived as weak person if you speak openly about problems.
Friends is one of the series that come to mind when I try to offer more mechanisms for long-term psychological adaptation.
The series highlighted the small moments of friendship between men.
As much as it helps the objective, external intervention, through the telephone, people arriving at times of despair, long-term support comes from family and close friends.
